17/05/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska's (RS) main opposition group, the Serb Democratic Party (SDS), demanded on Tuesday (16 May) that the RS legislature discuss an alleged assassination plot against RS Prime Minister Milorad Dodik. 
SDS says parliament must know what steps the government plans to take in light of the allegations. 
RS Interior Minister Stanislav Cadjo says only that a group of people was arrested recently and interrogated for suspicious activities. 
One remains in custody.
Also Tuesday, RS President Dragan Cavic called on Bosnian Serb parties to join forces in the Federation of BiH (FBiH) for the October general elections. 
Cavic said he sent letters to the Union of Independent Social Democrats, the Party of Democratic Progress and the Socialist Party of RS, inviting them to negotiations on a possible coalition.
In other news, a senior military delegation led by the Chief of the BiH Joint Staff, Lieutenant General Sifet Podzic, kicked off a visit to the United States on Tuesday. 
BiH's defence reforms will be one of the topics discussed during his trip. 
(Nezavisne novine - 17/05/06; NTV Hayat, RTRS, Srna - 16/05/06)
